data.rules:
Beat the game.

data.name: 20 exit
data.rules:
timing begins on gaining control of Mario and ends on peach appearing after bowser defeat; complete the game in the fastest way

since you keep your powerups, lives, and score upon deleting a file, you need to make sure to be small mario upon starting a run, and drop any powerups in the inventory box immediately after starting the run; any # of lives, coins, and points is fine, infinite lives cheat(C222-D4DD) is also ok

Beat all levels.

data.name: Any%
data.rules:
Any% ends when the player defeats the boss of the level: Forgotten Acropolis and does not require any switch palaces to be pressed. 
Timing starts when you exit the pipe in the intro screen.
To be played on the most up to date version (Current Version: 1.2/1.21)

100% requires all levels in the game to be beaten to trigger the credits. This includes the three switch palaces, the level Backtrack Passage and the final level Stormcrow's Alcazar.
This category DOES NOT require you to collect the Dragon Coins in Celestial Rex.
Timing starts when you exit the pipe in the intro screen.
To be played on the most up to date version (Current Version: 1.2/1.21)

data.name: any%
data.rules: Complete the game from Bowser to Xen's Castle, skipping the normal exit in Bridge of Panga. Timer ends after landing the last hit on FryGuy (at whistle).

data.name: backwards%
data.rules: Complete the game from Bowser to Yoshi's House. Timer ends after Mario hits the message block in Yoshi's House
Complete the game from Bowser to Xen's Castle, also completing Akihabara. Timer ends after landing the last hit on FryGuy (at whistle).

data.name: Any%

data.name: 100% True Ending
data.rules: Timer begins upon selecting a 1-player game and ends upon reaching the "Congratulations" screen with a picture of Mallow the Cat. (First frame the screen is visible.) All exits must be completed.
